label("$5$", (A + D)/2, E);
label("$h$", (A + P)/2, W);
[/asy]

Then by Pythagoras on right triangles $APB$, $APC$, and $APD$, \begin{align*}
AB^2 &= x^2 + h^2, \\
AC^2 &= (8 - x)^2 + h^2, \\
25 &= (4 - x)^2 + h^2.
